						               													<description>Here's $40 million.  Produce a movie.  Crew-up.  Get a Director +Actor +5 Crew cards to win.  It's all in the Cards.  It's your backstage pass to movie-making.  Strategic-Competitive-No Trivia&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is a Producer.&amp;#10;1.  Game play starts by dealing each Producer one 'Budget Card'&amp;#10;    'Budget Cards' range from $36-$43 million, in 4 different genres)&amp;#10;2.  Deal each Producer 3 'Crew Cards'  &amp;#10;    (For groups over 5, deal 4 'Crew Cards' each)&amp;#10;3.  Stack Action Deck + Crew Deck in middle of table.&amp;#10;4.  Producer with the lowest budget goes first.&amp;#10;    a.  Pickup 'Crew Card'&amp;#10;    b.  Then discard a 'Crew Card' from your hand to optimize your hand. Discarded card forms your Discard pile.  Each Producer will have a Discard Pile.&amp;#10;    c.  Read Action Card aloud to everyone....do what it says.&amp;#10;5.  Play continues clockwise.&amp;#10;    All future turns gets to select a Crew Card from the Deck or from the top card of another Producer's discard pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Winning Hand is:&amp;#10;    7 Crew Cards (Actor+Director in your genre, plus 5 Crew)&amp;#10;    No Duplicates&amp;#10;    Stay on or under budget&amp;#10;&amp;#10;FYI -&amp;#10;1.  getCrewd is built for anyone who's watched one movie&amp;#10;2.  Game is packaged in a round retro-style Hollywood film can&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
